description.narrative: The project development objective is to improve competitiveness of selected domestic supply chains, increase non-traditional agricultural exports and increase rice production in project areas.

The Recipient shall have entered into an agreement with the FOS

title.narrative: At least 5 subprojects for each of the five targeted supply chains in the domestic market have been funded through the Matching Gran t mechanism and implemented

comment.narrative: 289 sub-projects are under implementation in the targeted supply chains (Banana, green bean, mango, onion, sweet potato, tomato,red meat, poultry and processed food).

title.narrative: One-third of farming families engaged in exports crops have implemented #Origine Senegal# good agricultural practices guide based on GlobalGAP Protocol

comment.narrative: Approximately 881 farming families supported by sub-projects use good irrigation practices guides.

title.narrative: Non-traditional agricultural exports in project areas reach 12,000 tons by end of project

comment.narrative: As of March 31, 2014, exports have reached 5,535 tons in the project area by project beneficiaries. The end-of-project target isexpected to be met

title.narrative: At least 2,500 ha have been developed or improved by small farmers and agribusiness SMEs

comment.narrative: The end-of-project target has been exceeded.

title.narrative: Local production of banana covers 50% of domestic consumption

comment.narrative: The end-of-project target has been exceeded.

title.narrative: Local production of onion covers 75% of domestic consumption

comment.narrative: End-of-project target is likely to be exceeded. 374 sub-projects are currently in the pipeline for improved onion domestic supplychain.

comment.narrative: Actual number of hectares rehabilitated for rice production.

title.narrative: Total length of water catchments constructed

comment.narrative: Studies for the design of a master plan for the 5,000 ha are underway. The procurement process for the completion of 9 watercatchments is almost completed.

title.narrative: Increased annual production of rice paddy (tons) by 52,000 tons at the end of the project

comment.narrative: Out of the 6,963 hectares rehabilitated, 6,342 ha were cultivated during the 2013/2014 rainy season (1,771 ha) and 2013 dry season(5,571 ha). The cumulative production over both periods have reached reached 46,975 tons of paddy as of March 31, 2014. Cultivatedareas and productions increased compared to the previous year, especially for 2013 dry season.

title.narrative: Small ruminants productivity reach 20% in targeted farms at the end of the project
Swine productivity reach 40% in targeted farms at the end of the project
